"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-826411?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit">照片：Rafael Henrique/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p><em>摘自 7 月 27 日发给通过 Google 销售广告的公司的电子邮件：</em></p><p>尊敬的广告管理合作伙伴：</p><p> 2023 年 8 月 30 日，Google 将更新 Google 发布商限制中关于令人震惊内容的政策，以纳入游戏图像的例外情况。在游戏图像的背景下，如果内容描述了酷刑、性暴力、针对未成年人的暴力、针对突出现实的暴力行为，则该内容仅被视为“包含可怕、图形或令人厌恶的帐户或图像”或“描述暴力行为”。指名道姓，或基于与系统性歧视或边缘化相关的特征对个人或群体实施暴力。 。 。 。</p><p>请查看更新以确定它是否会影响您的网站或应用程序。如果您的网站或应用程序之前因令人震惊的内容而受到广告投放限制，但您认为更新后广告投放不应再受到限制，您可以在 2023 年 8 月 30 日或之后请求对您的网站或应用程序进行审核或提出申诉。 了解更多请求复审或上诉。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 22:07:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/notable-quotable-google-and-shocking-content-ads-app-site-gaming-gameplay-dd903a33</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/notable-quotable-google-and-shocking-content-ads-app-site-gaming-gameplay-dd903a33<category>广告</category><category>令人震惊的</category><category>形象的</category><category>地点</category><category>上诉</category><category>谷歌</category><category>赌博</category><category>视频游戏</category><category>互联网搜索引擎</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>技术</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>生活/生活方式</category><category>个人技术</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>社论</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>日常新闻</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>活的</category><category>生活方式</category><category>个人技术</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>社论</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>常规新闻</category><category>互联网搜索引擎</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Greece Has Its Eye on an Upgrade]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>在经历了 13 年的垃圾级评级之后，该国可以恢复投资级地位，帮助总理基里亚科斯·米佐塔基斯履行其改革使命。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11221797970291203701404590119993266500892"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11221797970291203701404590119993266500892"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name">Afroditi Xydi</span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name">Georgios Laskaris</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 30 日下午 5:49 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/greece-has-its-eye-on-an-upgrade-democracy-stability-recovery-merit-hiring-entrepreneurship-f366a754"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-826371?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 7 月 25 日，希腊总理基里亚科斯·米佐塔基斯在雅典。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Imago/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>经过近十年的危机后，希腊正在显现出稳定和复苏的迹象。在6月25日的选举中，中右翼政党新民主党在执政四年后再次当选，使该国走上了体制重组、市场主导的经济增长和扩大社会支持的道路。</p><p>评级机构将研究新政府的第一步举措。如果希腊表现出充分的经济改革和财政可持续性，预计希腊将在经历 13 年的垃圾级评级后于 2023 年恢复投资级状态。</p><p>再次当选的总理基里亚科斯·米佐塔基斯拥有千载难逢的机会来解决希腊的结构性和制度性挑战，加速该国的现代化。凭借<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/greek-conservatives-on-course-for-emphatic-election-win-d7dc0582?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">40.6% 的选票</a>、300 个议会席位中的 158 个席位以及反对派的减少，总理有权进行改革。他应重点关注通过改革教育、支持创业、培育高潜力经济部门和解决人口挑战等方式为经济和社会奠定坚实的基础。</p><p>近几十年来，停滞不前的大学教育一直困扰着希腊。希腊最好的大学在全球<a href="https://www.usnews.com/education/best-global-universities/greece" target="_blank" class="icon none">排名第250位</a>，毕业生失业率在经济合作与发展组织中<a href="https://www.oecd.org/newsroom/unemployment-rates-oecd-updated-may-2023.htm" target="_blank" class="icon none">名列前茅</a>。为了应对这些挑战，新民主党于 2022 年通过了一项法律，通过实行择优聘用教师、设立英语系​​和促进创业来改善公立大学。</p><p>实施这些改革需要瓦解主导大学管理的根深蒂固的政治联盟——尽管有政治成本，但仍应实施这一干预措施。这将使高成就人才能够在当地蓬勃发展，而不是移民到国外，并将高质量的研究成果用于商业。</p><p>与欧洲其他大部分国家不同，希腊仍然禁止私立大学，米佐塔基斯应该跨党派动用他的一些政治资本，以确保在议会获得结束禁令所需的 180 票。这样的变化将有助于扭转教授和研究人员的人才外流，创造高等教育的竞争，并吸引来自世界各地的学生。随着大学的重组，课程应扩大以培养管理和行政技能，这将支持经济的快速增长。</p><p>新冠疫情过后，希腊成为欧盟增长最快的经济体之一，国内生产总值<a href="https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/NY.GDP.MKTP.KD.ZG?locations=EU" target="_blank" class="icon none">增长 5.9%</a> 。 2019年至2022年间，新民主党的亲商方针帮助<a href="https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/BX.KLT.DINV.WD.GD.ZS?locations=GR" target="_blank" class="icon none">外国直接投资占GDP的比重从2.4%提高到3.1%</a> ， <a href="https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/NE.EXP.GNFS.ZS?locations=GR" target="_blank" class="icon none">出口从41%提高到</a>49%。这些政策预计将继续下去，但如果司法系统不变得更有效率，投资者信心和经济效率将继续受到限制。在这方面，希腊应利用技术扩大司法培训，并将法官的晋升与年度评估挂钩。</p><p>劳动生产率仍然是一个问题，希腊在欧盟<a href="https://data.oecd.org/lprdty/gdp-per-hour-worked.htm" target="_blank" class="icon none">排名接近垫底</a>。解决方案的一部分是在欧盟<a href="https://www.europarl.europa.eu/RegData/etudes/BRIE/2022/729366/EPRS_BRI(2022)729366_EN.pdf" target="_blank" class="icon none">复苏和弹性基金</a>22 亿欧元的支持下提高数字化水平。发展希腊与企业家重新建立的关系是另一个机会。希腊应该通过促进私人研发、支持初创企业出口以及在学术界、工业界和政府之间建立联系来成为创新中心。</p><p>希腊经济仍然很大程度上依赖旅游业， <a href="https://insete.gr/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/2020-2021_EN.pdf" target="_blank" class="icon none">旅游业贡献了19%</a>的GDP和17%的就业。为了实现经济多元化并避免过度旅游的诅咒，希腊可以利用其战略优势，即其位于三大洲交汇处的地理位置。利用其制造能力和物流基础设施，该国应该吸引更多公司在其境内扩大生产。除了成为物流中心之外，希腊还可以通过增加可再生能源生产、扩大与中东和欧洲的电力联系以及创建气候创新中心，成为清洁能源中心。</p><p>人口挑战也迫在眉睫。由于每名妇女的出生率低于 1.5，预计到 2050 年，希腊人口将从 1060 万下降到 880 万。新成立的家庭和社会凝聚力部需要不仅仅关注对家庭的经济激励和增加儿童保育的机会，以解决社会结构问题。鉴于议会中出现了两个极右翼政党，这将很困难。</p><p>除了促进男女平等外，政府还应扩大收养权并促进移民融入社会。至少三百万的希腊侨民也可以成为解决方案的一部分。简化入籍程序、遣返人才以及吸引有希腊血统的学生将启动人口扩张。</p><p>米佐塔基斯先生说他是一位改革者，他的记录表明他是有效的。在全世界注视着希腊试图重新获得投资级地位的同时，米佐塔基斯先生应该着手进行全面改革，以重新定位该国的 21 世纪发展方向。</p><p> <em>Xydi 女士和 Laskaris 先生是 Desmos 政策研究所的联合创始人。</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 21:49:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/greece-has-its-eye-on-an-upgrade-democracy-stability-recovery-merit-hiring-entrepreneurship-f366a754</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/greece-has-its-eye-on-an-upgrade-democracy-stability-recovery-merit-hiring-entrepreneurship-f366a754<category>希腊</category><category>危机</category><category>评级机构</category><category>改革</category><category>创业精神</category><category>招聘</category><category>优点</category><category>选举</category><category>恢复</category><category>稳定</category><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>经济增长/衰退</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>希腊</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>基里亚科斯·米佐塔基斯</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>经济增长</category><category>经济衰退</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>观点</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Hunter Biden, FARA and Unequal Justice]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>针对特朗普同伙的一项恶劣法律现在困扰着拜登总统的儿子。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11786258192805913745104590114352058306666"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11786258192805913745104590114352058306666"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 30 日下午 4:35 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-foreign-agents-registration-act-robert-mueller-donald-trump-26596b5a"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=FC59727D-1CAC-40DC-AD8D-4441776A4FF7&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fhunter-biden-foreign-agents-registration-act-robert-mueller-donald-trump-26596b5a&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">杂志社论报道：真正的问题是他的父亲是否参与其中。图片：Getty Images/William J. Hennessey, Jr. 综合：Mark Kelly<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div><p>不平等正义已成为亨特·拜登认罪协议的一个主题，上周法官玛丽莲·诺雷卡在法庭上询问检方和辩方，他们的协议是否意味着总统的儿子仍可能因违反《外国代理人登记法》而受到起诉。亨特的律师说不，但检察官说是，如果亨特根据该法规受到起诉，亨特可以感谢罗伯特·穆勒。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> 《FARA》是一项长期被忽视的法律，该法律可追溯至 1938 年，特别检察官穆勒 (Mueller) 将其拿出来，试图从唐纳德·特朗普 ( <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">Donald Trump</a> ) 的同伙那里窃取信息。它要求美国人在大多数情况下作为“外国委托人的代理人”向美国政府登记。正如我们当时指出的，截至 2016 年的近半个世纪里，司法部仅提起了 7 起 FARA 刑事案件，并赢得了 3 起定罪。起诉的罕见性给法律如何以及何时适用造成了很大的混乱。</p><p>但这并没有阻止穆勒先生。作为调查不存在的俄罗斯勾结的特别检察官，他利用《外国代理人登记法》起诉特朗普的同事，这些人大多被指控代表外国政府在工作中撒谎。</p><p>这就是他对付保罗·马纳福特（Paul Manafort）的方法，后者从乌克兰人那里拿走了钱。迈克尔·弗林 (Michael Flynn) 承认在根据 FARA 提交的有关其代表土耳其政府工作的文件中做出了虚假陈述。 FARA 还诱捕了格雷格·克雷格（Greg Craig）——一位权力很大的民主党律师、奥巴马总统的前白宫法律顾问——他因穆勒对马纳福特与乌克兰交易的调查而被起诉。</p><p>只要 FARA 的目标是特朗普身边的人，民主党人就会对这些起诉欢呼雀跃。当联邦陪审团因与《外国代理人登记法》相关的指控而宣判克雷格无罪时，他们甚至没有感到困惑，而我们和其他人认为这些指控根本不应该提出。</p><p>他们可能会对这一法律标准感到遗憾，因为联邦检察官已向诺雷卡法官确认，仍然可以对总统的儿子提出《外国代理人登记法》指控。根据穆勒先生的起诉，亨特很容易受到攻击。</p><p>我们知道亨特设立了一家空壳公司与中国华信能源开展业务，并且他没有注册为外国代理人。空壳公司是掩饰所有权的常见策略，接受外国实体的资金通常需要进行 FARA 注册。关于亨特在乌克兰的交易也存在类似的问题。</p><p> FARA 起诉对拜登总统具有政治影响。让他的儿子在他们乘坐空军二号一起前往相关国家时充当外国特工，会让总统声称对亨特的生意一无所知的说法更加令人难以置信。这肯定会成为他 2024 年竞选连任的一个问题，尤其是因为奥巴马政府的工作人员对亨特在乌克兰能源公司布里斯马 (Burisma) 董事会的高薪工作发出了危险信号。</p><p> FARA 从未被明确定义，并且是选择性使用的。这就是坏法律的定义，检察官很容易利用它来对付他们的政敌。</p><p>民主党人有理由说，如果华盛顿所有违反《外国代理人登记法》的人都受到起诉，那么一半的游说者就会破产。但如果他们在罗伯特·穆勒（Robert Mueller）忙着用它来对付他们的政敌时提出这个论点，那将是一个更有说服力的论点。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 20:35:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-foreign-agents-registration-act-robert-mueller-donald-trump-26596b5a</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-foreign-agents-registration-act-robert-mueller-donald-trump-26596b5a<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>美国政府</category><category>玛丽莲·诺瑞卡</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Rising Demand for School Choice]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>一些州报告称，代金券或 ESA 申请数量大幅增加。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11277182998813654381604590100122165004394"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11277182998813654381604590100122165004394"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 30 日下午 4:34 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-rising-demand-for-school-choice-arizona-florida-implementation-esa-1c47ce5f"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-822303?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">图为佛罗里达州希尔斯伯勒县一辆校车。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：玛莎·阿森西奥·莱茵/祖玛出版社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>许多州最近创建或扩大了择校计划，但家长是否抓住了这个机会？现在还为时过早，但来自几个州的数据应该会鼓励立法者相信强大的产品是有需求的。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>印第安纳州今年的优惠券计划增加了约 20%。根据州教育部门的数据，2022-23 年有超过 53,000 名学生参加，而上一学年有 44,376 名学生参加。另外还有 13 所私立学校被纳入其中，使总数达到 343 所。所有这一切都是在国家 5 月份通过提高收入上限和取消其他限制<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/indiana-budget-school-vouchers-republicans-school-choice-todd-huston-ecac3c5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">使学券几乎普及</a>之前发生的。</p><p>佛罗里达州今年还取消了收入限制，普及了 K-12 奖学金。非营利管理组织“Step Up for Students”最近表示，已颁发了 268,221 份基于收入的奖学金，高于一年前同期的 183,925 份。该组织表示，还发放了 74,711 份特殊需要奖学金，增加了约 15,000 份。</p><p>亚利桑那州在普及教育储蓄账户（ESA）方面比佛罗里达州领先一年。该州表示，2023 年批准了 47,667 名新生申请，而扩招前为 5,103 名。近 700 所私立学校接受 ESA 资金。</p><p>西弗吉尼亚州的 ESA 项目向所有已经在公立学校就读的学生开放，该项目已进入第二年。根据州财政部长的说法，该计划已收到 6,323 份下一学期的申请，高于去年的约 3,600 份。</p><p>据爱荷华州州长 Kim Reynolds 办公室称，爱荷华州<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/utah-school-choice-bill-iowa-education-savings-accounts-kim-reynolds-spencer-cox-11674860799?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">新的 ESA 计划</a>在一个月的时间内收到了 29,025 份申请。阿肯色州教育部称，阿肯色州已有近 5,000 名学生和 80 多所学校已经申请或开始申请<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/school-choice-arkansas-oklahoma-sarah-huckabee-sanders-kevin-stitt-wyoming-f34b237?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">另一个新的 ESA 系统</a>。申请于六月下旬开始，并持续到七月。爱荷华州和阿肯色州的计划在第一年并未普及，但随着它们逐步扩大资格范围，它们可能会扩大。</p><p>所有这些都不应促使各国固步自封。曼哈顿研究所最近的一份报告指出，让欧洲航天局穿越政治丛林只是第一步。许多家长<a href="https://edchoice.morningconsultintelligence.com/assets/206515.pdf" target="_blank" class="icon none">并不知道</a>他们所在州的这些服务，如果法律执行得不好，也起不了多大作用。 <a href="https://manhattan.institute/article/implementing-k-12-education-savings-accounts" target="_blank" class="icon none">作者写道</a>：“我们担心有 10 万个家庭想要参与该计划，但无法登录支付平台，或者无法跟踪他们的支出，或者无法及时向帮助其孩子的教育机构付款。”</p><p>一些州可能还会发现私立学校的座位需求超过了供应。但随着时间的推移，对 ESA 慷慨的州鼓励各种选择来扩大或开放，无论是基于信仰的、古典的、蒙特梭利的还是新的，并让家庭选择最适合他们的选择。这就是未来择校的样子。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 20:34:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-rising-demand-for-school-choice-arizona-florida-implementation-esa-1c47ce5f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-rising-demand-for-school-choice-arizona-florida-implementation-esa-1c47ce5f<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>欧洲航天局</category><category>亚利桑那</category><category>择校</category><category>合格</category><category>学生</category><category>执行</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>教育</category><category>私立教育</category><category>学校</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>教育</category><category>私立教育</category><category>学校</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[J.B. Pritzker, Public Union Boss]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>伊利诺伊州州长用纳税人的钱为他的 Afscme 盟友大幅加薪。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11786258192805913745104590112480283626838"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11786258192805913745104590112480283626838"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 30 日下午 4:33 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/j-b-pritzker-public-union-boss-government-worker-taxpayers-raise-wages-jobs-base-pay-illinois-30ed9f04"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824494?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">伊利诺伊州州长 JB Pritzker 六月</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：泰勒·格拉斯科克/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>反对政府工作人员进行集体谈判的最佳论点是，没有人代表纳税人。工会主席和他们支持的政治家坐在谈判桌上的双方。上周，伊利诺伊州州长 JB Pritzker 与美国州、县和市政雇员联合会 (Afscme) 签署了一份巨大的新合同，这再次证明了这一点。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>该合同涵盖未来四年，为 35,000 名公职人员提供 19.28% 的加薪，超过了私人工资的增长。这比卡车司机从联合包裹服务公司获得的丰厚新合同中为终身司机获得的收入还要多，而这仅仅是 Afscme 基本工资的增加。许多工人将根据工作任期获得更多加薪。</p><p>该合同还包括向每位批准合同的工人提供 1,200 美元的“津贴”。普利茨克在 2019 年的最后一份合同谈判中纳入了这些奖金，据称是为了补偿在前州长布鲁斯·劳纳 (Bruce Rauner) 领导下担任州政府工作人员的经济“困难”。 （还记得当州长试图代表纳税人时吗？）工会喜欢这种甜味剂，所以现在它已成为一种预期的刺激。</p><p>普利茨克周二在推特上表示，“伊利诺伊州是一个彻头彻尾支持工人的州。”他的意思是如果你为政府工作。那么私营经济中的工人呢？他们现在面临着更高的工会支出，这将在工资增加的基础上推高公共医疗和养老金的成本？据伊利诺伊州政策研究所称，普利兹克先生表示，新合同将在四年内耗资 6.25 亿美元，涨幅比之前的合同高出 61%。</p><p> Afscme工人已经拥有私营经济中很少存在的健康保险计划，新的四年期合同承诺工人第一年保费增长为零，第二年每月增加10美元，每月增加8美元在第三年和第四年。这相当于四年内每月只需 26 美元。猜猜谁会支付差额，因为健康保险费用上涨得更快。</p><p>伊利诺伊州的公共养老金已经是美国资金最不足的国家之一，而新的工资增长将使情况更加严重。养老金是根据工人职业生涯结束时的工资来计算的，因此工资的大幅上涨现在会转化为以后的巨额付款。记住一点：当伊利诺伊州的养老金变得难以负担时，民主党人将要求联邦纳税人提供救助。</p><p>工会在伊利诺伊州占据主导地位，因为普利兹克先生和州民主党人本质上是为为连任竞选活动提供资金的工会工作。工会工人的大幅加薪意味着更多的工会会费支付，这意味着为提供加薪的政客提供更多的竞选捐款。这就是为什么允许政府工作人员进行集体谈判对国家的财政和经济健康具有如此大的破坏性。</p><p>普利兹克希望在明年夏天于芝加哥举行的民主党全国代表大会上发挥重要作用，如果拜登总统决定不参选，他很可能亲自竞选总统。这也是州长表现得更像工会老板而不是所有伊利诺伊州公民的领导者的另一个原因。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 20:33:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/jb-pritzker-public-union-boss-government-worker-taxpayers-raise-wages-jobs-base-pay-illinois-30ed9f04</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/jb-pritzker-public-union-boss-government-worker-taxpayers-raise-wages-jobs-base-pay-illinois-30ed9f04<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>联盟</category><category>提高</category><category>私人工资</category><category>工作</category><category>政府</category><category>政府工作人员</category><category>纳税人</category><category>支付</category><category>伊利诺伊州</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>一般劳工问题</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>地区政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>一般劳工问题</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>地区政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Gary Gensler’s Money-Market Gamble]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>美国证券交易委员会的第三次基金改革尝试带来了新的金融风险。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB10950590414055573352804590092263504202740"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB10950590414055573352804590092263504202740"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 30 日下午 4:32 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sec-money-market-fund-regulation-gary-gensler-hester-peirce-d15048bb"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818831?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">美国证券交易委员会主席加里·詹斯勒</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Al Drago/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>监管机构很少承认错误，但你瞧，美国证券交易委员会本月废除了两项货币市场规则。唉，主席加里·詹斯勒 (Gary Gensler) 的重写可能会在金融问题到来时给短期融资市场带来更大压力。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>自 2008 年金融恐慌以来，美国证券交易委员会第三次试图制定法规，以防止优质货币市场基金挤兑。这些基金投资于优质商业票据和短期政府证券。它们应该保持稳定的价值，投资者可以随时赎回其股票。</p><p>大公司和机构投资者使用这些基金来管理现金流，它们通常提供比单独投资于政府证券的基金更高的收益率。它们还为大银行和企业提供流动性来源。但当市场面临压力时，它们也很容易受到挤兑的影响。</p><p> 2008 年雷曼兄弟的倒闭引发了储备初级基金的挤兑，该基金失去了每股 1 美元的挂钩。其他基金的投资者陷入恐慌，短期信贷市场冻结。财政部和美联储在政府担保下突然介入。</p><p>美国证券交易委员会 (SEC) 于 2010 年发布了规定基金持有期限、信用质量和流动性要求的规则。四年后，SEC 要求机构投资者的优质基金报告浮动的资产净值，而不是稳定的每股 1 美元的价格，这给投资者带来了错误的安全感。我们支持这个规则。</p><p>不过，美国证券交易委员会同时通过了另外两项规则，允许基金经理在流动性低于一定阈值时暂停赎回并征收提款费。目标是制止恐慌。但正如我们警告的那样，这些规则将激励投资者在市场压力出现的第一个迹象时就撤回资金。</p><p>你知道什么？这就是 2020 年 3 月发生的事情。在大流行的不确定性中，基金经理试图通过亏损出售长期证券来将流动性维持在 SEC 门槛之上。这些抛售导致短期信贷市场再次失灵，并促使政府再次干预。美国证券交易委员会 (SEC) 目前正在废除 2014 年允许基金暂停赎回并对赎回收取费用的规定。</p><p>然而，下次金融市场面临压力时，詹斯勒的调度可能会引发更多动荡。新规定将基金经理在一个工作日内能够变现的最低资产份额从10%提高到25%，在一周内从30%变现到50%。当机构优质基金的每日赎回量超过基金资产的5%时，机构优质基金的管理人还需要向撤回投资者收取费用。</p><p>就连美国证券交易委员会也承认这些规则可能会自食其果。赎回费用和更高的流动性要求“可能会降低他们能够向投资者提供的收益率”，并且“可能导致更多的资本从优质资金重新分配到政府基金、银行存款账户和其他类型的流动性工具”，424 -页面规则制定注释。</p><p>美国证券交易委员会还警告称，合规成本可能“以更高的费用比率或减少某些基金产品的可用性的形式转嫁给基金投资者。”这些成本可能“有助于基金行业的整合”，并减少商业票据发行人和投资者的选择。</p><h4> ***</h4><p>美国证券交易委员会承认，总而言之，新规则“可能会降低优质货币市场基金作为资产类别的生存能力”。然而，它表示，将现金重新分配给受保银行产品和政府货币市场基金“可能是有效的”。推动更多投资者进入政府基金可能有助于在美联储量化紧缩期间支撑国债市场。但这些规则也可能降低市场整体的弹性。 “我们的目标之一是消灭优质基金吗？”共和党委员海丝特·皮尔斯（Hester Peirce）提出异议。</p><p> “今天的通过包含了与 2014 年货币市场基金规则制定相同的缺陷——坚持认为我们自己的判断优于货币市场基金、其保荐人、董事会和股东的判断，”她写道。 “更好的方法是允许基金选择适合自己的方法。</p><p>这种一刀切的监管往往会造成系统性金融脆弱性，只有在市场陷入困境时，这种脆弱性才会显现出来。当我们发现根斯勒先生是否比市场更聪明时，可能已经为时已晚了。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 20:32:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/sec-money-market-fund-regulation-gary-gensler-hester-peirce-d15048bb</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/sec-money-market-fund-regulation-gary-gensler-hester-peirce-d15048bb<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>证券交易委员会</category><category>加里·詹斯勒</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[AI’s Growing Legal Troubles]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>如果没有第 230 条的保护，版权问题和诽谤诉讼就会不断出现。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590114034250533418"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590114034250533418"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/andy-kessler"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/B3-BS035_Kessle_AM_20180912114138.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/andy-kessler" itemprop="url" rel="author">安迪·凯斯勒</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 30 日下午 4:15 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ais-growing-legal-troubles-section-230-publisher-class-action-9efaf374"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-826031?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit">照片：Cfoto/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>哇，那速度真快。仅用了八个月就找到了 ChatGPT 和生成人工智能的致命弱点。不，这不是幼稚的管理，尽管 OpenAI 首席执行官 Sam Altman 确实宣称人工智能对人类构成了“灭绝的风险”，并实际上恳求参议院司法小组委员会监管人工智能，然后当欧盟真正通过法规时，他威胁要撤出该地区。</p><p>不，这不是白宫，人工智能的高级管理人员通过白宫做出了耻辱的举动，允许拜登总统从他们那里获得自愿为人工智能提供安全护栏的承诺。一个承诺！这比小指的承诺更强还是更弱？</p><p>这也不是联邦贸易委员会最近写给 OpenAI 的一封钓鱼探险信，要求该公司提供所有工作的微小细节。嗯，奥特曼先生当然是这么要求的。鉴于 FTC 最近在很多案件中都处于败诉状态，也许该公司应该让 ChatGPT 来写答案。</p><p>相反，人工智能的致命弱点是传统的媒体问题。首先是版权。像 ChatGPT、Google 的 Bard 和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/META" class="">Meta</a><span class="company-name-type">的</span>Llama 这样的工具都是大型语言模型，这意味着它们通过读取服务器上的所有内容来输入多达万亿个参数，包括维基百科、以前称为 Twitter 的 snark 污水池以及来自 Twitter 的活泼 Reddit。 《Roaring Kitty》和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GME" class="company-name">《GameStop》</a>名声大噪。难怪 ChatGPT 如此容易产生幻觉。社交媒体公司现在希望获得报酬，并限制对其内部的扫描。</p><p>今天的搜索结果中显示的受版权保护的片段被视为合理使用。但是，OpenAI、谷歌或 Meta 是否可以合法地扫描版权材料并从中创建全新内容，或者生成式 AI 的输出是否被视为“衍生品”，需要原始版权所有者的许可？我们即将在一系列版权诉讼中找到答案。喜剧演员兼作家 Sarah Silverman 本月加入了针对 OpenAI 和 Meta 的集体诉讼，声称他们“复制和摄取”受版权保护的材料并创建了“衍生”版本。</p><p>事实证明，OpenAI 扫描了巨大的书籍存储库，名为 Books1 和 Books2，让人想起苏斯博士的 Thing 1 和 Thing 2。OpenAI 没有透露 Books2 中的内容，其中可能包含超过 300,000 本书。 Ms. Silverman&#39;s enjoined suit says these “shadow libraries” are “flagrantly illegal.”</p><p> Novelists Paul Tremblay and Mona Awad have sued OpenAI, claiming ChatGPT does a great job summarizing their books and can do that only because it scanned them. I asked ChatGPT about specifics inside a few of my books, and it gave good answers. I may be caught in the same net. This may also be true for artists—Stability AI is being sued by Getty Images and others for scanning their libraries and using them as a basis for AI-generated images resulting from text prompts.</p><p> You may have heard that ChatGPT is increasingly good at writing code. Just over a week ago, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MSFT" class="company-name">Microsoft</a> started charging $30 a month for its AI assistant, Copilot. Maybe that will help pay a potential $9 billion in damages claimed by programmer and, it turns out, lawyer Matthew Butterick, who filed a class-action suit against Microsoft and OpenAI on behalf of open-source programmers for use of copyrighted code.</p><p> Copyright is a headache, but defamation liability can be a lobotomy. Recall that social-media companies and cloud services are protected under Section 230 of the 1996 Communications Decency Act. Those that host content aren&#39;t liable for what is said on their services, but the publishers are. Without Section 230, there would be no Twitter or Facebook.</p><p> But tools like ChatGPT don&#39;t host things, they create things. They&#39;re publishers. No Section 230-like protections exist for them. Radio host Mark Walters is suing OpenAI for defamation, saying it accused him of embezzling from a nonprofit. He may have a case.</p><p> The new and increasingly valuable AI industry desperately needs legal protection—let&#39;s call it Section 230.ai. But these companies foolishly launched without it. The lobbying money floodgates will soon open to try to get something through Congress. It might cost more than that White House pledge. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4> Read More Inside View</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/esg-is-blowin-in-the-wind-protest-songs-60s-70s-companies-capitalism-187f5ce4?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">ESG Is Blowin&#39; in the Wind</a> <span class="date">July 23, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-innovation-cage-match-facebook-twitter-competition-musk-ai-794e0ebf?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">The Innovation Cage Match</a> <span class="date">July 16, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-bidenomics-blather-populist-election-free-market-union-price-controls-economy-7048dae0?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">The Bidenomics Blather</a> <span class="date">July 9, 2023</span></li></ul></div></div><p> Corporate America is cautious. I&#39;ve heard of companies not allowing ChatGPT on company-issued laptops. They are worried about their proprietary code and intellectual property being stolen by AI tools and probably similar liability issues.</p><p> Among Microsoft, Google and late-entry players <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AAPL" class="company-name">Apple</a> and</p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AMZN" class="">Amazon</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> there is more than $8 trillion in market capitalization for the class-action wolves to chase. AI is a sitting duck. AI is the future and will drive the economy&#39;s next leg of productivity and wealth creation, but the rush to market with tools neither ready for prime time nor strictly legal will slow rollout.真丢脸。 These companies should protect their Achilles by fixing AI&#39;s legal vulnerabilities pronto.<p></p><p> Write to kessler@wsj.com.</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 20:15:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ais-growing-legal-troubles-section-230-publisher-class-action-9efaf374</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ais-growing-legal-troubles-section-230-publisher-class-action-9efaf374<author><![CDATA[Andy Kessler]]></author><category> ai</category><category> language model</category><category> coypright</category><category>诽谤</category><category>section 230</category><category> liability</category><category>出版商</category><category>平台</category><category>derivative</category><category> fair use</category><category>人工智能技术</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>社交媒体平台/工具</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>人工智能/机器学习</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>计算机科学</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>科学/人文</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>人工智能</category><category>机器学习</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>计算机科学</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>科学</category><category>人文学科</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>人工智能技术</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体</category><category>娱乐</category><category>社交媒体平台</category><category>工具</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[AMLO Plays a Shell Game With Pemex]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> The oil giant gets a government rescue, helping bondholders at Mexicans&#39; expense. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590108383357849718"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590108383357849718"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/mary-anastasia-ogrady"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/B3-BI562_ogrady_AM_20180807122707.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/mary-anastasia-ogrady" itemprop="url" rel="author">Mary Anastasia O&#39;Grady</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 30, 2023 4:14 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/amlo-plays-a-shell-game-with-pemex-mexico-explosion-debt-corruption-rescue-oil-production-9eb55e0a"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-826369?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Mexico&#39;s President Andrés Manuel López Obrador in Tepic, Mexico, July 28.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: MEXICO PRESIDENCY/via REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> When a July 7 <a href="https://www.infobae.com/mexico/2023/07/07/impactantes-imagenes-asi-fue-el-incendio-de-la-plataforma-de-pemex-en-campeche-videos/" target="_blank" class="icon none">explosion</a> rocked an offshore production complex belonging to Petróleos Mexicanos, or Pemex, the state-owned company&#39;s bonds also felt the boom. A week later came a Fitch <a href="https://www.fitchratings.com/research/corporate-finance/fitch-downgrades-pemex-idrs-to-b-on-rating-watch-negative-14-07-2023" target="_blank" class="icon none">downgrade</a> , followed by a Moody&#39;s decision to shift its outlook on Pemex to “negative” from “stable.”</p><p> The Mexican government had been reluctant to backstop Pemex debt. But on Thursday CEO Octavio Romero announced that the Mexican treasury will step in to refinance the company&#39;s liabilities. The rescue will cut Pemex&#39;s cost of borrowing by about half but does nothing to alleviate the company&#39;s mismanagement, corruption, inefficiency and politicization. It might make things worse by removing market pressure. But it is an admission that Pemex can&#39;t dig itself out of its $107 billion debt hole.</p><p> The blast on the Nohoch-A link platform in the Cantarell Field was caught on video. As heavy black smoke billowed above the inferno, emergency boats fitted with water cannons rushed to put out the flames. Rescue crews evacuated more than 320 workers. Two private contractors died in the accident, and one is missing.</p><p> Pemex said it shut down nearly “all the wells in the area” and lost 700,000 barrels of oil production. By Saturday afternoon the company claimed it had recovered 600,000 barrels of production capacity. Still, the accident was more than a hiccup at Pemex, once a beloved symbol of Mexican nationalism.</p><p> For Fitch it may have been the last straw. On July 14 the rating agency reduced Pemex “issuer default ratings” to B+ from BB-. The agency also said it is downgrading “approximately $80 billion of Pemex&#39;s international notes outstanding to &#39;B+/RR4 from &#39;BB-.&#39; ”</p><p> Fitch said the downgrade “reflects the environmental and social impact associated with multiple accidents at Pemex&#39;s operating facilities since February 2023.” It also cited concerns about “the Mexican government&#39;s ability and willingness to materially improve the company&#39;s liquidity position and capital structure in the next two years without concessions from creditors.”</p><p> Maturing debt of more than $15 billion this year and next, Fitch said, means refinancing “will expose the company to higher interest expense,” putting stress on cash flow. “An inability to refinance the capital markets debt with similar or other long-term financial instruments would exacerbate its liquidity risk by the end of 2024.”</p><p> At a morning press conference last week, Mexico&#39;s President Andrés Manuel López Obrador <a href="https://www.bloomberglinea.com/english/amlo-downplays-fitch-moodys-downgrade-of-pemex/" target="_blank" class="icon none">pooh-poohed</a> the Fitch rating as meaningless and said the latest accident was exaggerated in the media. But Mr. Romero&#39;s announcement later in the week that the state will take over the role of raising money for the company looks like a direct response to deepening investor concerns that the company is a bad credit bet.</p><p> When Mr. López Obrador took office in December 2018, Mr. Romero <a href="https://www.reuters.com/article/mexico-oil/mexico-targets-oil-output-of-2-6-mln-bpd-by-end-2024-pemex-idUSE1N1VF01A" target="_blank" class="icon none">said</a> that by the end of the president&#39;s six-year term Pemex&#39;s daily crude production would reach more than 2.624 million barrels. In June crude production was 1.56 million a day including from partnerships.</p><p> Mr. López Obrador blames Pemex&#39;s underperformance on company management under previous administrations—and on the 2014 energy reform that opened the market to limited competition. Naturally his solution is to pack the company with loyalists and try to restore its monopoly power in drilling and also in downstream activities like refining. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4> Read More Americas</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/amlo-makes-xochitl-a-household-name-mexico-presidential-election-coalition-64299752?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">Mexico&#39;s AMLO Makes Xóchitl a Household Name</a> <span class="date">July 16, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colonial-joe-biden-bullies-a-neighbor-populism-election-guatemala-populism-race-south-america-d4ab1cdb?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">Colonial Joe Biden Bullies a Neighbor</a> <span class="date">July 9, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russias-many-spies-in-mexico-war-global-power-network-putin-south-america-b4b3659f?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">Russia&#39;s Many Spies in Mexico</a> <span class="date">July 2, 2023</span></li></ul></div></div><p> The government has canceled bidding rounds for new investment in oil exploration and drilling. Blocking private capital means forgoing additional oil output from the country and the commensurate tax and royalty revenue.</p><p> Pemex&#39;s six refineries use only 54% of installed capacity. But AMLO built a new refinery in Dos Bocas, Tabasco, anyway. It cost $20 billion, twice the original estimate, and has yet to start up. Potential competitors in gasoline aren&#39;t able to get permits to build filling stations or import supply. This hurts the broader Mexican economy: By refusing to comply with treaty obligations under the US-Mexico-Canada Agreement and domestic law, the government discourages investment in other areas. Nearshoring has brought new manufacturing interests to Mexico but not nearly what might be if there were confidence in the rule of law.</p><p> In May Reuters <a href="https://www.reuters.com/markets/commodities/mexicos-gasoline-independence-dream-sinks-dirty-fuel-oil-glut-2023-05-31/" target="_blank" class="icon none">reported</a> a sharp increase in the production of high-sulfur “fuel oil,” a byproduct of antiquated and inefficient refineries. The inability to process this hydrocarbon stream means the company either has to export it—losing value—to more technologically advanced refineries in places like the US or to burn it for electricity generation despite the heavy pollution it leaves behind.</p><p> Bond investors are celebrating the government intervention that set off a <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-07-28/pemex-debt-gains-as-mexico-throws-4-billion-lifeline-to-driller?utm_source=google&amp;utm_medium=bd&amp;cmpId=google#xj4y7vzkg" target="_blank" class="icon none">rally</a> in Pemex debt. But by explicitly shifting the fiscal burden of a company that operates like a government bureaucracy onto the Mexican federal budget, AMLO has made Mexicans poorer.</p><p> <em>Write to O&#39;Grady@wsj.com.</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 20:14:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/amlo-plays-a-shell-game-with-pemex-mexico-explosion-debt-corruption-rescue-oil-production-9eb55e0a</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/amlo-plays-a-shell-game-with-pemex-mexico-explosion-debt-corruption-rescue-oil-production-9eb55e0a<author><![CDATA[Mary Anastasia O’Grady]]></author><category>墨西哥</category><category>pemex</category><category> borrowing</category><category>腐败</category><category>mismanagement</category><category> rescue</category><category>爆炸</category><category>rating agency</category><category> offshore production</category><category>活力</category><category>Fossil Fuels</category><category> Integrated Oil/Gas</category><category> Oil and Gas</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Octavio Romero</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>活力</category><category>fossil fuels</category><category> integrated oil</category><category>气体</category><category>oil and gas </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ashes to Ashes, Disney to Dust]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Archaeologists will one day puzzle over the remains of this strange civilization. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11754030163052123715304590114373803390784"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11754030163052123715304590114373803390784"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Philip Terzian</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 30, 2023 4:13 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ashes-to-ashes-disney-to-dust-florida-california-collapse-attendance-theme-park-525e3b4d"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-826045?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Visitors at Disneyland Resort in Anaheim, Calif., Jan. 22, 2015.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Jae C. Hong/Associated Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Attendance is declining at the four Disney World theme parks, the Journal recently <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-world-crowds-universal-studios-florida-36b0a579?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">reported</a> .魔法王国 7 月 4 日的平均等待时间比 2019 年缩短了 20 分钟。这让我很惊讶，也一定让总部的诉讼感到不安。但出于同样的原因。由于我不是迪士尼股东，我承认我对这个消息感到某种病态的满足。</p><p> I was 5 when the original Disneyland opened for business in the summer of 1955. I had faithfully followed its progress on ABC&#39;s “Walt Disney&#39;s Disneyland,” and there was no 5-year-old in America more primed to make the pilgrimage. But growing up in suburban Washington, my odds of a cross-country family trek to Orange County, Calif., were nonexistent.</p><p> In 1982, however, my wife and I moved to Los Angeles, where we were met by an old friend who was a longtime Disneyland enthusiast and insisted on escorting us there. It was interesting to see the place outside the confines of black-and-white television. My wife adored the singing birds in the Tiki Room, and the interminable wait for Space Mountain confirmed my lifelong terror of roller coasters. I saw and heard the animatronic (and slightly disconcerting) Abraham Lincoln, and I purchased a Donald Duck watch, which still runs. Because my friend and I had met in the Reuters Washington bureau during Watergate, we made sure to take the Jungle Cruise, where President Nixon&#39;s beleaguered press secretary, Ron Ziegler, had once famously worked as an operator.</p><p> Yet by the end of the day I had to concede that I was probably 27 years too late. My 5-year-old self almost certainly would have been enthralled by the experience, just as I had responded to the avuncular Walt Disney. But Uncle Walt was long dead. At 32, I found myself only mildly entertained by Disneyland, even comfortably bored at times, and harried by a curious thought all afternoon that remains my most vivid memory: What would archaeologists, digging feverishly a thousand years hence, make of the place?</p><p> It couldn&#39;t go on forever. The fossilized remnants of ersatz creatures, the urban swamps and labyrinthine paths, the shards of souvenirs and mysterious inscriptions (“Tomorrowland”), the electronic carcasses, the miniature castle with its gothic façade and interior wiring—what kind of hybrid civilization was this? It was evidently visited by millions every year, but to what end? And why had this self-styled “magical” land not expanded beyond its asphalt perimeter?</p><p> I&#39;m fairly certain that I didn&#39;t share these questions with my friend—which would have been impolite and, surrounded as we were by massive swarms of visitors, improbable. But the famous, the familiar and the seemingly indestructible have a way of disappearing in due course. And even as long ago as 1982 the decline and fall of this particular phenomenon may not have been foreseen but could have been predicted.</p><p> I just didn&#39;t expect the evidence to emerge so soon.</p><p> <em>Mr. Terzian is the author of “Architects of Power: Roosevelt, Eisenhower, and the American Century.”</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 20:13:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ashes-to-ashes-disney-to-dust-florida-california-collapse-attendance-theme-park-525e3b4d</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ashes-to-ashes-disney-to-dust-florida-california-collapse-attendance-theme-park-525e3b4d<category>迪士尼乐园</category><category>disney world</category><category> attendance</category><category>人气</category><category>theme park</category><category> Broadcasting</category><category> Cable Broadcasting</category><category> Entertainment Venues</category><category> Amusement/Theme Parks</category><category> Leisure/Arts/Hospitality</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>Archaeology</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>科学/人文</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>archaeology</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>科学</category><category>人文学科</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>观点</category><category>broadcasting</category><category> cable broadcasting</category><category> entertainment venues</category><category> amusement</category><category> theme parks</category><category>闲暇</category><category>艺术</category><category>款待</category><category>媒体</category><category>娱乐</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Flirting With Danger’ Review: Heiress Undercover]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Marguerite Harrison was perfect for the job: beautiful, charming, intelligent, fluent in French and German, with an exceptionally good memory. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590108174236205124"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-826380?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Marguerite Harrison during the filming of “Grass.”</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Alamy Stock Photo </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590108174236205124"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Moira Hodgson</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 30, 2023 4:12 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/flirting-with-danger-review-heiress-undercover-4c12601e"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> In April 1920 a Baltimore heiress was arrested in Russia, accused of being a secret agent. Marguerite Harrison (1879-1967), whose wedding trousseau had numbered 40 outfits, now wore lice-infested clothes and a pair of men&#39;s shoes. Imprisoned without trial, she would spend 10 months in Moscow&#39;s notorious Lubyanka jail, including time in solitary confinement.</p><p> The daughter of a shipping magnate, Marguerite had grown up with all the trappings of her class: tutors, governesses, piano lessons, debutante balls and annual trips to Europe. She could have led a pleasant if uneventful life,punctuated by garden parties, games of bridge and nights at the opera. Instead, driven by an insatiable thirst for adventure and an almost pathological attraction to danger, she became a spy. She was perfect for the job: beautiful, charming, intelligent, fluent in French and German, with an exceptionally good memory. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/schemas/1f9e1d53-d9f2-4bac-a4b6-d1f795204366.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Her mother, Elizabeth, had hoped that Marguerite would marry a landed European aristocrat; those dreams were dashed when Marguerite fell in love with Tom Harrison, a man Elizabeth despised. Tom came from a prominent but penniless Baltimore family. The couple married in 1901 and had a son the next year. After Tom died of a brain tumor in 1915, Marguerite went to work at the Baltimore Sun as a society reporter, then as a cultural critic. When America joined World War I in 1917, she wrote patriotic stories to boost support. But she felt restless working in the newsroom and wanted to go to the front. In the fall of 1918, she volunteered to join Military Intelligence, using the newspaper as a cover.</p><p> The war ended in November, so she was sent to Paris to attend the peace talks. She proved to be a clever, politically astute reporter and, with her considerable social connections, a valuable intelligence officer. She was prescient about the effect the harsh armistice terms would have on Germany. She took mental notes and filed reports to Military Intelligence, dropping them off with contact agents in hotels or using a cipher book to send cables of coded messages.</p><p> In “Flirting With Danger: The Mysterious Life of Marguerite Harrison, Socialite Spy,” Janet Wallach presents a compelling story that pulsates with the energy of a thriller. She describes how Harrison, the first American woman to get into Germany after the armistice, found the country in shock. There were clashes between the Communist-leaning Spartacists and the right-wing Freikorps, a paramilitary group of former soldiers. Count Harry Kessler, a former German ambassador to Poland, summed up the situation: “The German people, starved and dying by the hundred thousand, were reeling deliriously between blank despair, frenzied revelry and Revolution. Berlin had become a nightmare, a carnival of jazz bands and rattling machine guns.” Harrison narrowly escaped being shot by crossfire in the street.</p><p> By her own admission, Harrison “was not a Marxist or even a Socialist.” Yet she wondered, Ms. Wallach tells us, whether the Bolsheviks “could provide some answers to the great unrest in the world.” Her great desire was to visit Russia. A visa was refused. Undaunted, in February 1920 she slipped across Poland&#39;s eastern border. In Moscow, the head of the foreign office seemed to accept her credentials as a journalist. He surprised her by saying he was glad about Prohibition in America. He believed that workers, unable to go to saloons and drink, would “flock to political meetings” instead, spreading the popularity of communism. Two months after that friendly encounter, Harrison was arrested. Thanks to a mole in the US intelligence service, the Russians had known about her for some time. To obtain her release, she agreed to remain in Moscow as a double agent.</p><p> Here the story gets murky. How much damage she inflicted is impossible to assess, but several of Harrison&#39;s acquaintances blamed her for their subsequent arrests. Nevertheless, before long, Harrison was back in the Lubyanka.</p><p> Ms. Wallach, whose previous books include “Desert Queen: The Extraordinary Life of Gertrude Bell” (1996) and “The Richest Woman in America: Hetty Green in the Gilded Age” (2012), relies heavily on Harrison&#39;s autobiography, “There&#39;s Always Tomorrow” (1935), and other books to tell her story. Harrison recounts her Russian experience in “Marooned in Moscow” (1921), an oddly dispassionate memoir. “The Liberation of Marguerite Harrison” (2020), a biography by Elizabeth Atwood, a former editor at the Baltimore Sun, is at times dubious of Harrison&#39;s accounts, noting that after she left Russia, she whitewashed her prison experiences.</p><p> Harrison was very much at home with the Russians, whether they were Communists or Czarists. “The unflappable newswoman who suppressed her feelings and admitted she &#39;felt afraid to form close ties,&#39; even with her young son, found the Russians&#39; exuberance irresistible,” Ms. Wallach writes. Among other things, Harrison loved their generosity and their “Oriental sense of hospitality.”</p><p> The Russian fiasco did not erode Harrison&#39;s self-confidence or her enthusiasm for danger. In 1923 she set off on a 46-day trek to make “Grass,” a documentary about the remote Bakhtiari tribe in present-day Iran. Each year about 5,000 Bakhtiaris and their 50,000 animals would make a procession through the treacherous mountain passes of southwest Persia in search of green pastures. Harrison stars in the film, directed by her friend Merian Cooper, who would later make “King Kong.” But “Grass” was a cover for an espionage mission. The Bakhtiari controlled land that had large reserves of oil.</p><p> Despite the occasional cliché and at times cloying prose (during her wedding, Harrison is said to have eyes that were “dancing like soft clouds in a dazzling sky”), Ms. Wallach tells a good story. Harrison&#39;s adventures over seven years—trips to the Baltics, China, Japan, Manchuria, Turkey and across Siberia—make for exciting reading. However, the woman herself proves elusive. Why was she driven to undertake such risks? She wasn&#39;t a zealot and doesn&#39;t seem to have had any strong political beliefs. So what motivated her? She is opaque, well used to hiding things. As Ms. Wallach writes, “spies have their own truths.”</p><p> <em>Ms. Hodgson is the author of “It Seemed Like a Good Idea at the Time: My Adventures in Life and Food.”</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 20:12:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/flirting-with-danger-review-heiress-undercover-4c12601e</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.